        },
        "FIGREF1": {
            "text": "Figure 2: A. Continuous aerosol suction is performed via a suction tube (white arrows) inserted into the open side of the box, resulting in negative pressure-box. B. An oxygen-insufflated nasal tube (green arrows) inserted into the upper side of the box helps to maintain patient respiration.",
            "type": "figure"
        }
